==English==

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# The act or condition of [[prostrate|prostrating]] oneself, as a sign of humility.
# A part of the ordination of Catholic and Orthodox priests.
#:''The ordination ceremony includes a variety of rituals, rich in meaning and history, e.g., the '''prostration''', laying on of hands, anointing of hands, giving of the chalice and paten, and sign of peace.'' — [http://www.dor.org/vocations/faqs_ordination.htm Diocese of Rochester, NY]
# Being laid face down ([[prone]]).
# The condition of being prostrated, as from heat.


====Usage note====
Outside of ordination, prostration as a sign of humility has never been part of the Western tradition, but was present in the Middle-Eastern and Asian traditions. 

